abstract.value: The Julie Gilbert Papers are the materials the writer used while researching her biography <emph render="italic">Opposite Attraction: The Lives of Erich Maria Remarque and Paulette Goddard</emph>.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations should take the following form: <lb/><lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Julie Gilbert Papers; MSS 038; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.
Julie Gilbert donated her papers in July 1998.

Julie Gilbert was born on July 21, 1949 in New York. Her father, Henry Goldsmith was a publisher and her mother, Janet, was an actress. She attended Boston University and has worked as a professional actress, writer and teacher. She has written biographies, novels and plays including <title render="italic">Umbrella Steps,</title>which became a film, and <title render="italic">Ferber: The Biography of Edna Ferber and Her Circle,</title>which was nominated for the National Book Critics Circle Award. She received a Pulitzer Prize nomination for <title render="italic">Opposite Attraction,</title>the result of the research contained in this collection.
Includes audiocassettes, mini-cassettes and floppy disks containing recorded interviews, notes and drafts of the biography.
